column5: Got a job interview at 8:30 in Bracebridge. Hoping to hit a lake for either lakers, pike, whities, walleye, or anything bigger than panfish. Will be mid morning to noon start and afternoon finish. Will be walking and no hut. Don't wanna walk too far as my time is limited.  Thanks guys

i would be heading straight for lake joe if i were you, anywhere you fish you'll get fish, the lake is a laker factory!! If you don't wanna walk far foots bay would most likely be your best bet, the bite is always good there but the fish are mostly 1-3 pounders there are 5-15 pounders out there but much more of those little guys but they are tons of fun!

You don't wanna walk far with the way conditions are right now, lol.
Where would be best to park for a short walk at Foot`s Bay. I`m probably gonna head there.
A little bit further but not much if your going to Joe would be Parry Sound. One of the best ice fishing lake trout destinations there is. 100 ft from the parking lot and your into them.
It's a little out of the way. Got an interview in Bracebridge at 8:30 am and just want to hit something close foe a few hours to try out my new to me x67c
Try lake Muskoka ... Boyds Bay just a few miles from Bracebridge on 118 ... Pickereye
lake Joe is great anytime of year
